    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="upa.00077.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">431 Stevens St.</name>
                    <name type="place">Camden N J, U S A</name>
                    <date when="1884-02-12" rend="right">Feb 12 '84</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Herb</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Thanks for your affectionate letter&#8212;(thank your dear mother also for
                hers&#8212;a most welcome one)<ptr target="upa.00077_n1"/>&#8212;Nothing special or
                new to write about&#8212;health &#38; every thing go on with me ab't as
                usual&#8212;I enclose <hi rend="underline">a piece of cloth</hi><ptr
                    target="upa.00077_n2"/>&#8212;cannot find a <hi rend="underline">coat</hi> that I think would serve you,
                (which is the garment I suppose you most want)&#8212;Dr Bucke<ptr target="n0119"/>
                has told me of a picture he got from you, he prizes immensely&#8212;I havn't seen
                it&#8212;Write whenever you can, dear boy, &#38; I will to you&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
            <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="upa.00077.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text> 
